Response Text: Re: AIPP - watching the drama over the art at the new airport.  As I understand how it works, the amount set aside for AIPP in a new build/construction is based on a % of the total budget of the project.  With today's escalating prices in construction material, it would be better for the City to say a % of the budget with a not to exceed amount for AIPP.  OR - in lieu of spending all that money on the art for one project, some % goes into 'savings' to help with maintenance, repairs and perhaps purchasing AIPP in other smaller, lower-budgeted projects.  While I support the AIPP, with some of these larger projects, you are spending SO MUCH on the art, that you have to scale back in the design or construction of the project.  I think the entire AIPP program needs to be completely overhauled.

